Abstract
The advancement of Industry 4.0 technologies has transformed conventional manufacturing into intelligent and highly connected production environments. Modern industrial machines continuously generate sensor data that can be analyzed to identify equipment degradation before failures occur. Predictive maintenance has emerged as an effective strategy to reduce maintenance costs, improve equipment reliability, and minimize production downtime.
This project presents a predictive maintenance system for 6G-enabled smart manufacturing using the Isolation Forest algorithm. Manufacturing sensor data was preprocessed and enhanced through feature engineering techniques, including rolling averages, sensor deviations, maintenance score decay, and production efficiency metrics. The trained anomaly detection model generated anomaly scores that were further categorized into Low, Medium, and High maintenance risk levels.
An interactive Streamlit dashboard was developed to visualize machine performance, maintenance alerts, anomaly trends, sensor behavior, production analysis, and historical risk progression. The dashboard enables maintenance engineers to monitor machine health effectively and prioritize maintenance activities before failures occur.
The proposed system demonstrates how machine learning can improve maintenance planning, reduce operational costs, and increase manufacturing efficiency in Industry 4.0 environments.
Keywords: Predictive Maintenance, Smart Manufacturing, Industry 4.0, 6G Networks, Isolation Forest, Anomaly Detection, Streamlit Dashboard, Machine Learning.
