Chapter 2: Problem Statement
Manufacturing industries frequently experience unexpected equipment failures that disrupt production schedules and increase maintenance costs. Traditional monitoring systems rely on manually defined threshold values for individual sensors. However, normal operating conditions vary across different machines, operating modes, and production environments, making fixed thresholds ineffective for identifying subtle changes in machine behavior.
Early indicators of equipment failure are often hidden within complex multidimensional sensor data and cannot be detected through conventional monitoring techniques. Consequently, maintenance teams may fail to recognize emerging faults until significant performance degradation or equipment failure has already occurred.
To address these challenges, an intelligent predictive maintenance system is required that can automatically learn normal machine behavior, identify abnormal operating conditions, estimate maintenance risk, and provide actionable insights to maintenance engineers.
