Chapter 7: Feature Engineering
Feature engineering is one of the most important stages in predictive maintenance because raw sensor values alone often fail to capture abnormal machine behavior.
Several engineered features were developed to better represent machine conditions.
7.1 Rolling Average Features
Rolling averages were computed for each machine using a moving window.
The following rolling features were created:
•	Rolling Temperature 
•	Rolling Vibration 
•	Rolling Power Consumption 
•	Rolling Error Rate 
These features represent the normal operating behavior of each machine.
________________________________________
7.2 Sensor Deviation Features
The deviation between the current sensor reading and its rolling average was calculated.
The following deviation features were created:
•	Temperature Deviation 
•	Vibration Deviation 
•	Power Deviation 
•	Error Deviation 
These features help identify sudden changes in machine behavior.
________________________________________
7.3 Vibration-to-Power Ratio
A new feature representing the relationship between vibration and power consumption was developed.
Machines experiencing abnormal vibration while consuming normal power often indicate early mechanical wear.
________________________________________
7.4 Maintenance Score Decay
The Predictive Maintenance Score was transformed into a Maintenance Decay feature.
Higher decay values indicate decreasing machine health.
________________________________________
7.5 Error Trend
The difference between consecutive Error Rate values was calculated.
This feature identifies machines whose operational errors are increasing over time.
________________________________________
7.6 Production Efficiency
Production Efficiency was computed using the ratio of production speed to power consumption.
Machines producing fewer units while consuming higher power may indicate declining operational performance.
________________________________________
Benefits of Feature Engineering
The engineered features provide several advantages:
•	Capture temporal behavior. 
•	Identify gradual machine degradation. 
•	Improve anomaly detection performance. 
