Chapter 12: Maintenance Risk Classification
To support maintenance planning, anomaly scores were converted into maintenance risk categories.
The following thresholds were used:
Anomaly Score	Maintenance Risk
0.00 – 0.39	Low Risk
0.40 – 0.69	Medium Risk
0.70 – 1.00	High Risk
Low Risk
Machines classified as Low Risk exhibit normal operating conditions and do not require immediate maintenance.
Medium Risk
Medium Risk machines show early signs of abnormal behavior and should be monitored more frequently.
High Risk
High Risk machines demonstrate significant deviations from normal operating patterns and should be prioritized for preventive maintenance.
