This internship project successfully developed an intelligent predictive maintenance system for a 6G-integrated smart manufacturing environment. By combining feature engineering, the Isolation Forest algorithm, and an interactive Streamlit dashboard, the system detects abnormal machine behavior, classifies maintenance risks, and provides actionable insights for proactive maintenance planning. The project demonstrates practical applications of machine learning in Industry 4.0 and highlights how data-driven decision-making can improve manufacturing efficiency, reduce operational downtime, and optimize maintenance resources.

